Cherry tomato and Bocconcini pizzas
via Russell Jenkins (and Donna Hey)

base
1 teaspoon dried yeast
3/4 teaspoon caster sugar
3/4 cup (185ml) lukewarm water
1 1/2 cups (225g) plain all-purpose flour
1/2 teaspoon sea salt flakes
2 teaspoons olive oil

topping
3 x 250 g punnets cherry tomatoes
1/4 cup oregano leaves, chopped
sea salt and cracked black pepper
1 cup (100g) grated mozzarella
1/4 cup (20g) finely grated parmesan
180g bocconcini, drained and torn
100g baby rocket (arugula) leaves, to serve

Place the yeast, sugar and water in a bowl and mix to combine. Set aside for 5 minutes or until bubbles appear on the surface.

Place the flour, salt and oil in a bowl and make a well in the centre. Add the yeast mixture, stirring with a knife until a dough forms.

Turn out onto a lightly floured surface and knead for 5 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
Place in a bowl, cover with a damp cloth and set aside for 30 minutes or until doubled in size.

Preheat oven to 230C (415F).

To make the topping, crush the tomatoes, oregano, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Divide the dough into 4 portions and roll out each to a 14cm round.

Place on baking trays and top with mozzarella, parmesan, boccocini and
tomatoes. Cook for 12â€“15 minutes or until the bases are crispy and golden.

Top with rocket to serve. Makes 4.
